  <section id="education">
    <h2>Crypto Education Basics</h2>
    <div class="edu-item">
      <h3>What is Cryptocurrency?</h3>
      <p>Cryptocurrency is digital money secured by blockchain technology. It allows for decentralized transactions without the need for traditional banks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="edu-item">
      <h3>What is Bitcoin?</h3>
      <p>Bitcoin is the first and most recognized cryptocurrency. It acts as a store of value and enables peer-to-peer transactions globally.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="edu-item">
      <h3>What is a Blockchain?</h3>
      <p>A blockchain is a public digital ledger that records transactions across many computers. It’s secure, transparent, and unchangeable.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="edu-item">
      <h3>Difference Between Bitcoin and Altcoins</h3>
      <p>Bitcoin is the original cryptocurrency. Altcoins are all others like Ethereum, Solana, and XRP, each with unique features and purposes.</p>
    </div>
    <img src="https://gray-decisive-stingray-220.mypinata.cloud/ipfs/bafy…2bie" alt="Crypto Coin Cluster" class="edu-image">
